\c 4
\s1 Tugas-tugas keturunan Kehat
\p
\v 1 Lalu berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada saya dan Harun,
\v 2-3 “Adakanlah sensus yaitu mencatat nama-nama semua laki-laki dari keempat kaum keluarga keturunan suku Lewi yang berusia antara tiga puluh sampai dengan lima puluh tahun. Mereka ini yang akan bertugas dalam Kemah Pertemuan.
\p
\v 4 Keturunan Kohat yang bertanggung jawab penuh atas segala sesuatu yang berkaitan dengan peralatan yang paling suci di Kemah Pertemuan.
\v 5 Pada waktu bangsa Israel sudah bersiap-siap untuk memindahkan tempat perkemahan, maka Harun dan anak-anaknya akan memasuki Kemah Pertemuan dan menurunkan tirai yang memisahkan tabut suci dari bagian Kemah Pertemuan yang lain. Mereka akan menutupi peti tersebut dengan tirai ini.
\v 6 Setelah itu, tirai tersebut harus ditutupi dengan pentutup yang terbuat dari kulit halus, dan di atasnya selebar kain berwarna biru menutupinya kemudian pengusung Tabut Perjanjian yang terbuat dari kayu akan dipasang.
\p
\v 7 Selanjutnya Harun dan anak-anaknya harus mengambil selembar kain biru yang lain untuk menutupi meja yang digunakan untuk mempersembahan roti kepada-Ku. Di atas selembar kain tersebut, Harun dan anak-anaknya harus meletakkan piring persembahan, mangkok-mangkok untuk kemenyaan, cangkir-cankir beserta kendi-kendi untuk anggur dan juga roti.
\v 8 Semuanya ini harus ditutupi dengan selembar kain berwarna merah, kemudian selembar kulit halus. Lalu mereka harus memasang kayu-kayu pengusung.
\p
\v 9 Selanjutnya mereka harus mengambil selembar kain biru lagi untuk menutupi kaki pelita, pelita-pelita, pemotong-pemotong sumbu, pemadam pelita dan baki-bakinya beserta semua tempat minyak zaitun yang digunakan untuk pelita-pelita.
\v 10 aki pelita beserta semua peralatan ini harus ditutup lagi dengan selembar kulit halus, dan diletakkan di atas sebuah bingkai yang digunakan untuk mengusungnya.
\p
\v 11 Harun dan anak-anaknya harus membentangkan seembar kain berwarna biru tua di atas mezbah emas, dan menutupinya lagi dengan selembar kulit halus. Semuanya itu harus dipasang pada kayu-kayu pengusungnya.
\p
\v 12 Semua peralatan Kemah suci yang masih tersisah harus dibungkus dengan kain biru tua, dan ditutupi dengan selembar kulit halus lalu diletakkan di atas bingkai pengusung.
\p
\v 13 Setelah itu, semua abu harus dipindahkan dari mezbah, dan mezbah itu harus ditutupi dengan selembar kain berwarna ungu.
\v 14 Semua peralatan mezbah harus diletakkan di atas kain itu - tempat-tempat api, garpu-garpu daging penyodok dan bejana pembasuhan. Kemudian mereka harus menutupi semuanya itu dengan selembar kulit halus dan memasang kayu pengusungnya.
\p
\v 15 Pada waktu Harun dan anak-anaknya sudah membongkar perkemahan, mereka harus masuk ke dalam kemah-Ku dan menutupi semua peralatan dan pelengkapan yang berada di tempat maha kudus. Sesudah itu, barulah orang-orang keturunan Kehat boleh masuk untuk memikulnya. Namun mereka tidak diperbolehkan melihat, mendekati atau pun menyentuh benda-benda tersebut karena semuanya sudah dikhususkan hanya untuk-Ku. Apabila mereka melakukannya, maka mereka akan mati. Untuk menjaga supaya orang -orang keturunan Kehat tidak terhapus dari suku Lewi, maka Harun bersama anak-anaknya harus memberi tugas secara terperinci tentang apa saja yang harus mereka bawa. Demikianlah tugas bagi orang-orang Kehat setiap kali kemah-Ku dipindahkan.
\p
\v 16 Eliezer, anak Harun yang menjadi penanggung jawab atas Kemah-Ku, minyak zaitun untuk pelita-pelita, kemenyaan yang sudah diberi rempah-rempah, persembahan sajian harian, dan minyak urapan. Dia juga bertanggung jawab atas seluruh kemah pertemuan, benda dan peralatan yang diadalamnya dan di dalam ruang maha kudus. ”
\p
\v 17 Lalu berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada Harun dan saya,
\v 18-20 “Jaga agar keluarga-keluarga suku Kohat tidak lenyap dari antara keturunan Lewi saat mereka mendekati benda-benda kudus, maka inilah yang harusescendants of Kohath approach the sacred items in the Sacred Tent\add to take them to another location\add*, Aaron and his sons must always go in with them and show each of them what work to do and what things to carry. But the descendants of Kohath must not enter the Sacred Tent\add at any other time\add* and look at the things that are in it. If they do that, I will get rid of all the descendants of Kohath.”
\s1 Tugas dan tanggung jawab keturunan Gerson
\p
\v 21 Berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada saya,
\v 22 “Write down the names of all the men who belong to the clans descended from Gershon.
\v 23 Write the names of the men who are between thirty and fifty years old. They will be men who will also do work at the Sacred Tent.
\p
\v 24 This is the work that they must do and the things that they must carry\add when you move to a new location\add*:
\v 25 They must carry the curtains of the Sacred Tent, they must carry the Sacred Tent and all the things that cover it, including the nice outer covering made from skins of goats, and the curtain which is at the entrance of the Sacred Tent.
\v 26 They must also carry the curtains that form the wall that surrounds the courtyard that surrounds the Sacred Tent and the altar, the curtain that is at the entrance to the courtyard, and the ropes\add that fasten the curtains\add*. They must also do the packing and loading of these things.
\v 27 Aaron and his sons will supervise the work of all the descendants of Gershom. That work includes carrying those things and doing other work that is necessary for moving them. They must tell each of the descendants of Gershom what things they must carry.
\v 28 Those are the tasks that you must give to the men who belong to the clans descended from Gershom. Aaron's son Ithamar is the one who will supervise their work.
\s1 The work of the men descended from Merari
\p
\v 29 Count also the men who belong to the clans descended from Merari.
\v 30 Write the names of the men who are between thirty and fifty years old. They will be men who will also work at the Sacred Tent.
\v 31 Their work will be to carry the frames that hold up the tent, the crossbars, the posts\add that hold up the curtains\add*, and the bases.
\v 32 They must also carry the posts for \add the curtains that form the wallsof\add* the courtyard and the bases for the posts, the tent pegs, and the ropes\add to fasten the curtains\add*. Tell each man what things he must carry.
\v 33 Those are the tasks that the descendants of Merari must do at the Sacred Tent. Aaron's son Ithamar is the one who will supervise them.”
\s1 Summary of the counting of the descendants of Levi
\p
\v 34 So Aaron and Moses/I and the Israeli leaders counted the descendants of Kohath, writing also the names of their clans and family groups.
\v 35 They/We counted all the men who were between thirty and fifty years old who were able to work at the Sacred Tent.
\v 36 The total was 2,750 men.
\v 37 They were the descendants of Kohath who \add were able to\add* work at the Sacred Tent. Aaron and Moses/I counted them just as Yahweh had commanded Moses/me.
\p
\v 38 They/We also counted the descendants of Gershon, writing also the names of their clans and family groups.
\v 39 They/We counted all the men who were between thirty and fifty years old who were able to work at the Sacred Tent.
\v 40 The total was 2,630 men.
\v 41 They were the descendants of Gershon who \add were able to\add* work at the Sacred Tent. Aaron and Moses/I counted them as Yahweh had commanded.
\p
\v 42 They/We also counted the descendants of Merari, writing also the names of their clans and family groups.
\v 43 They/We counted all the men who were between thirty and fifty years old who were able to work at the Sacred Tent.
\v 44 The total was 3,200 men.
\v 45 They were the descendants of Merari who \add were able to\add* work. Aaron and Moses/I counted them as Yahweh had commanded Moses/me.
\p
\v 46 So Aaron and Moses/I and the Israeli leaders counted all the descendants of Levi, writing also the names of their clans and family groups.
\v 47 They/We counted all the men who were between thirty and fifty years old. They were ones who\add were able to\add* work at the Sacred Tent and who carried the tent and everything that was connected with it.
\v 48 The total was 8,580 men.
\v 49 They/We completed the counting of \add all the descendants ofLevi\add*, as Yahweh had commanded Moses/me. And they/we told each man what work he was to do and what things he must carry\add when they moved to a new location\add*.